546
00:22:13.770 --> 00:22:19.150
But this sacrificial altar doesn't
belong to any of their zones.

547
00:22:15.110 --> 00:22:20.150
<b>Sacrificial Altar</b>

548
00:22:19.570 --> 00:22:22.320
In other words, it's a free area.

549
00:22:22.320 --> 00:22:25.990
It's fair game for
whoever gets here first.

550
00:22:26.450 --> 00:22:33.120
Of course, we normally wait
until after the ordeal ends in death.

551
00:22:33.120 --> 00:22:34.040
What?!

552
00:22:34.040 --> 00:22:36.460
Then, Luffy, Sanji, and Usopp are...?!

553
00:22:36.790 --> 00:22:38.420
Calm down.

554
00:22:38.420 --> 00:22:42.880
My presence here doesn't mean
your friends are dead...

555
00:22:43.470 --> 00:22:44.930
unfortunately.

556
00:22:45.550 --> 00:22:49.310
I came here for a completely
different reason.

557
00:22:49.310 --> 00:22:50.390
What?!

558
00:22:50.390 --> 00:22:51.470
A different reason...?

559
00:22:52.140 --> 00:22:55.850
So then, does that mean
we can get out of here

560
00:22:55.850 --> 00:22:57.860
if Luffy's group comes to rescue us?!

561
00:22:57.860 --> 00:23:00.320
Yeah, that's right...

562
00:23:00.820 --> 00:23:04.910
If you can escape
the free area, that is.

563
00:23:04.910 --> 00:23:05.740
What?

564
00:23:06.410 --> 00:23:08.870
Just hold that thought.

565
00:23:08.870 --> 00:23:12.120
The reason I came here is because,

566
00:23:12.120 --> 00:23:14.830
although those are
the normal rules for reckoning,

567
00:23:14.830 --> 00:23:18.500
when there's an exceptional situation,
they change a little.

568
00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:19.460
Exceptional...

569
00:23:19.460 --> 00:23:20.840
That's right.

570
00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:22.090
Case in point:

571
00:23:22.460 --> 00:23:28.510
Three sacrifices make an unauthorized
escape to the forest using vines.

572
00:23:28.510 --> 00:23:30.850
Huh... Does that happen?

573
00:23:32.470 --> 00:23:34.230
There's a god on this island, right?

574
00:23:34.230 --> 00:23:35.690
I'm gonna go meet him.

575
00:23:45.570 --> 00:23:48.280
This is all his fault!

576
00:23:49.450 --> 00:23:53.750
Someone has to die to atone
for the others' sin of escaping.

577
00:23:55.120 --> 00:23:58.170
Sacrifice is the truth of this world.

578
00:23:59.170 --> 00:24:02.800
This way, if they return,

579
00:24:02.800 --> 00:24:05.260
they will realize their individual faults

580
00:24:05.260 --> 00:24:08.260
when they see their friend dead.

581
00:24:11.010 --> 00:24:15.640
Offer your life to God!

582
00:24:17.600 --> 00:24:19.310
No way!

583
00:24:28.150 --> 00:24:29.200
Perish.

584
00:24:42.380 --> 00:24:45.050
Sorry to have kept you waiting!

585
00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:47.880
Sky Knight!

586
00:24:50.970 --> 00:24:53.680
It seems we are
entertaining a surprise guest!

587
00:25:01.310 --> 00:25:03.230
Gan Fall!

588
00:25:07.570 --> 00:25:10.780
Sky Knight!

589
00:25:10.780 --> 00:25:13.700
He is quite a skilled
and worthy opponent.

590
00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:16.490
Let's get a bit rougher
with him, Pierre.

591
00:25:18.870 --> 00:25:21.920
What’s that decrepit 
fossil doing here?!

592
00:25:22.380 --> 00:25:24.920
Shall we play with him a little, Fuza?!

593
00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:28.170
Do your worst!

594
00:25:28.170 --> 00:25:31.130
We don't need two gods
on this island!

595
00:25:39.600 --> 00:25:41.690
Go!

596
00:26:24.520 --> 00:26:30.110
Sky Knight!

597
00:26:40.620 --> 00:26:43.250
We need to give him
one more push, Pierre.

598
00:26:43.250 --> 00:26:44.620
Let's go!

599
00:26:50.510 --> 00:26:51.840
You son of a bitch!

600
00:26:54.130 --> 00:26:57.470
You probably came
here knowing this, but...

601
00:26:57.470 --> 00:27:00.930
you're a wanted criminal!

602
00:27:00.930 --> 00:27:06.440
Yes, you'll see how I deal with
aggravating fools like yourself!

603
00:27:09.270 --> 00:27:10.940
Ordeal of String!

604
00:27:30.710 --> 00:27:33.090
You're still alive?

605
00:27:33.090 --> 00:27:35.930
Impressive indeed!

606
00:27:35.930 --> 00:27:40.560
Well, then, as a reward, I'll give
you my prized finishing blow!

607
00:27:48.980 --> 00:27:51.110
Surprise Balls!

608
00:28:05.210 --> 00:28:10.210
<b>Shandian Settlement of Guerrillas</b>
<b>Village Hidden in the Clouds</b>

609
00:28:15.630 --> 00:28:16.590
Aisa!

610
00:28:19.510 --> 00:28:20.680
Where have you been?

611
00:28:21.550 --> 00:28:22.680
Kamakiri!

612
00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.930
Upper Yard again?

613
00:28:24.930 --> 00:28:27.560
You've got vearth
in your bag, don't you?

614
00:28:29.020 --> 00:28:30.940
Don't go there too often...

615
00:28:32.270 --> 00:28:34.190
or you'll lose your life.

616
00:28:38.320 --> 00:28:40.200
Don't tell me what to do!

617
00:28:40.780 --> 00:28:43.330
You haven't even beaten Enel yet!

618
00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:49.370
Damn brat.

619
00:28:50.500 --> 00:28:51.830
An opening?

620
00:28:51.830 --> 00:28:53.380
That's right.

621
00:28:53.380 --> 00:28:57.470
For some reason, Gan Fall
has entered Upper Yard.

622
00:28:57.470 --> 00:29:02.470
That old geezer thinks he can settle
everything in Skypiea peacefully.

623
00:29:03.260 --> 00:29:05.310
He's got it all wrong.

624
00:29:08.020 --> 00:29:10.100
Victory or defeat.

625
00:29:10.100 --> 00:29:13.270
Those are the only two
outcomes in a battle.

626
00:29:15.280 --> 00:29:17.650
The great warrior Kalgara said,

627
00:29:15.280 --> 00:29:19.740
<b>Warrior of Shandora Wyper</b>
<b>A Shandian</b>

628
00:29:17.650 --> 00:29:19.740
"Shine the Light of Shandora."

629
00:29:20.240 --> 00:29:22.740
We'll follow those words.

630
00:29:22.740 --> 00:29:26.540
It doesn't matter who
we have to fight—

631
00:29:26.540 --> 00:29:28.710
the former god Gan Fall or Enel.

632
00:29:28.710 --> 00:29:31.040
So long as they reign as god,

633
00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:37.210
they're all the same to us
no matter what form they take.

634
00:29:37.210 --> 00:29:40.800
They all have to be eliminated!

635
00:29:40.800 --> 00:29:41.970
Wyper.

636
00:29:43.050 --> 00:29:46.430
Someone on Angel Island
rebelled against Enel.

637
00:29:46.430 --> 00:29:48.060
I heard it was a young woman.

638
00:29:49.020 --> 00:29:52.810
This is the first rebel in the six years
since Enel began his reign.

639
00:29:52.810 --> 00:29:54.560
So what?

640
00:29:54.560 --> 00:29:58.190
Since Gan Fall saved her 
from reckoning,

641
00:29:58.190 --> 00:30:02.570
Enel now has a reason
to judge even the former god.

642
00:30:03.450 --> 00:30:05.530
Gan Fall has never harmed any of us,

643
00:30:05.530 --> 00:30:11.580
whether as the Sky Knight
or as the former god...

644
00:30:12.040 --> 00:30:15.340
nor has he tried to directly
confront Enel.

645
00:30:15.710 --> 00:30:20.130
But that same man has
finally entered Upper Yard.

646
00:30:20.630 --> 00:30:26.220
If he and a priest happen to kill
each other, so much the better.

647
00:30:26.220 --> 00:30:31.930
Or do you mean to say that
Gan Fall is no longer our enemy?

648
00:30:31.930 --> 00:30:34.440
When people have a common enemy,

649
00:30:34.440 --> 00:30:36.940
that they are now allies is a delusion!

650
00:30:39.860 --> 00:30:43.740
If you have doubts,
then stay out of the fight, Raki!

651
00:30:44.570 --> 00:30:46.240
You'll only get in our way!

652
00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:51.790
Aisa!

653
00:30:53.710 --> 00:30:57.040
What?! It's not like I went
to Upper Yard or anything!

654
00:30:57.790 --> 00:31:00.460
Don't go into the tent right now.

655
00:31:02.050 --> 00:31:07.890
Wyper– That is, the descendant of
the great warrior, Kalgara, is angry.

656
00:31:09.510 --> 00:31:11.850
Yeah, that's scary.

657
00:31:14.770 --> 00:31:16.400
He's scarier than God...

658
00:31:20.150 --> 00:31:21.650
Help...

659
00:31:21.650 --> 00:31:22.940
them?

660
00:31:24.200 --> 00:31:25.780
Us?

661
00:31:25.780 --> 00:31:28.450
Yes, that's right.

662
00:31:28.950 --> 00:31:32.870
Let's try to create a way for
them to escape somehow.

663
00:31:46.680 --> 00:31:48.970
I can't even tell what they're doing...

664
00:31:48.970 --> 00:31:50.050
Amazing!

665
00:31:52.350 --> 00:31:56.520
It seems my negotiations
with your group are over!

666
00:31:57.770 --> 00:32:00.110
You're as soft as ever!

667
00:32:01.940 --> 00:32:04.820
What... is this fight?

668
00:32:12.330 --> 00:32:14.450
Divine Reckoning...

669
00:32:15.960 --> 00:32:18.790
What that girl did was foolish.

670
00:32:20.250 --> 00:32:22.090
We should never...

671
00:32:22.670 --> 00:32:25.380
anger God Enel.

672
00:32:44.940 --> 00:32:46.650
Please come back...

673
00:32:47.070 --> 00:32:48.650
God!

674
00:32:56.450 --> 00:32:58.080
I've got you now.

675
00:33:03.590 --> 00:33:06.130
Is something wrong, Gan Fall?!

676
00:33:06.130 --> 00:33:08.420
What did you do?!

677
00:33:09.090 --> 00:33:11.640
Why?! Why can't we move?!

678
00:33:11.640 --> 00:33:13.550
A dying man...

679
00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:16.600
needs no answer.

680
00:33:29.570 --> 00:33:32.740
The mysterious Ordeal of String!

681
00:33:34.240 --> 00:33:35.830
Even you may enter Upper Yard,

682
00:33:35.830 --> 00:33:39.250
but you will be subject
to our trials all the same.

683
00:33:40.210 --> 00:33:44.210
Don't think that we
can be beaten so easily!

684
00:33:48.840 --> 00:33:50.340
God Enel...

685
00:33:51.720 --> 00:33:54.850
is a glorious and inaccessible being.

686
00:34:00.060 --> 00:34:01.440
That's right.

687
00:34:01.440 --> 00:34:04.560
The sacred ground will sing again...

688
00:34:04.560 --> 00:34:05.900
someday, for sure.

689
00:34:06.980 --> 00:34:08.480
Sky...

690
00:34:09.860 --> 00:34:13.070
Sky Knight!
